{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox Treaty | name = Inter-American Convention on The Forced Disappearance of Persons | date_signed = 9 June 1994 | location_signed = [[Belem do Para]], Brazil | date_effective = 28 March 1996 | condition_effective= 2 ratifications | signatories =16 | parties =15 | depositor = General secretariat of the [[Organization of American States]] | languages = Spanish, English, Portuguese and French | wikisource = }} The '''Inter-American Convention on The Forced Disappearance of Persons''' is a [[treaty]] of the [[Organization of American States]] (OAS) intended to combat the [[forced disappearance]] of persons. The Convention was adopted in 1994. Ratification is open to all members of the OAS and {{as of|2014|lc=y}}, the convention has been ratified by 15 states. Violations of the convention can be brought to the [[Inter-American Commission on Human Rights]].
{{as of|2014}}, the only state to have signed the convention but not ratified it is [[Nicaragua]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.oas.org/juridico/english/sigs/a-60.html|title=INTER-AMERICAN CONVENTION ON THE FORCED DISAPPEARANCE OF PERSONS|website=www.oas.org|access-date=2018-09-06}}</ref>
