'''Same-sex immigration policy in Brazil''' or [[immigration equality]] is [[legal]] in [[Brazil]] since December 3, 2003, and the new text is of January 29, 2008. The [[Federal Police Department|Federal Police of Brazil]], located in the Brazilian Airports, is the responsible by this initial procedure, that forwards the documents to the National Immigration Council of Brazil, located in [[Brasília]], the federal capital. Which examines whether the union is true, such as opposite-sex couples.

